# AthDGC · Zenodo DOI Minting Pack

Mint the DOI **first** - every other announcement should carry the DOI badge. Once the DOI exists you can put it on the website, the README, the data paper, the conference abstracts, and the mailing-list announcements.

There are two clean paths. **Path A (recommended)** wires GitHub to Zenodo so every future `git tag` automatically gets its own DOI. **Path B** is a manual Zenodo upload - use it if you want to mint a DOI before tagging anything.

---

## Path A - GitHub ⇄ Zenodo integration (auto-archive on every release)

### Step 1 · Sign in to Zenodo with GitHub

1. Go to **https://zenodo.org/login** and sign in with your GitHub account (the one that owns the `AthDGC` org).
2. Visit **https://zenodo.org/account/settings/github/**. You'll see a list of your repositories.

### Step 2 · Toggle ON the repo

3. Find `AthDGC/Diachronic-Linguistics-Platform` (or whichever repo you want to mint - you can mint multiple).
4. Flip the **ON** switch beside it. Zenodo now watches the repo for new releases.

