## Path B - Manual deposition (mint a DOI before tagging anything)

If you want a DOI right now and you're not ready to tag a release yet:

1. Go to **https://zenodo.org/uploads/new**.
2. Upload a placeholder file - even just a zipped snapshot of the GitHub repo. (`gh repo archive AthDGC/Diachronic-Linguistics-Platform --format=zip` will do it.)
3. Paste the metadata from the `.zenodo.json` above into the corresponding Zenodo form fields.
4. Set **Resource type** = *Dataset*, **License** = *Apache-2.0*, **Access right** = *Open*.
5. Click **Save**, review, then **Publish**.
6. You instantly receive a DOI.
7. Later, when you tag v0.1.0 on GitHub via Path A, link the new GitHub-triggered deposition as a **new version** of this manual deposition so the concept DOI is preserved.

