## After the DOI exists - same-day actions

1. Edit `athdgc.github.io` to show the DOI badge.
2. Edit the `README.md` of every AthDGC GitHub repo to show the DOI badge.
3. Update `athdgc_data_paper.md` (the short data paper) - substitute the DOI in the front matter and the citation block.
4. Post the LINGUIST List, HUMANIST, and CORPORA announcements (use the text from `athdgc_announcement.md`, prefixed with "DOI: [DOI pending Zenodo mint]").
5. Submit the data paper to the Journal of Open Humanities Data (or alternative - see paper front matter).
6. Schedule the bilateral emails (Haug, Passarotti, Dik, Crane, the Greek-diachronic and IE argument-structure circles) - paste DOI + paper preprint link.

